        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 18 at 1:15PM CST by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 115 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Decatur, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Decatur, Monticello, Mount Zion, Forsyth, Bement, Cerro Gordo,
Harristown, Long Creek, Atwood, Argenta, Oreana, Hammond, Cisco,
Decatur Airport, White Heath, Oakley, Lake City, Elwin, Milmine, and
Hervey City.

This includes Interstate 72 between mile markers 133 and 172.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
